p;class&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:152px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">0&nbsp;due&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;inherent&nbsp;class&nbsp;imbalance.&nbsp;Meaningful&nbsp;</span><span class="mtk1">predictions&nbsp;for&nbsp;class&nbsp;1&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:171px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">would&nbsp;require&nbsp;addressing&nbsp;this&nbsp;imbalance&nbsp;</span><span class="mtk1 bracket-highlighting-0">(</span><span class="mtk1">e.g.,&nbsp;through&nbsp;resampling&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:190px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">techniques&nbsp;or&nbsp;by&nbsp;adjusting&nbsp;class&nbsp;weights</span><span class="mtk1 bracket-highlighting-0">)</span><span class="mtk1">.</span></span></div><div style="top:209px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span></span></span></div><div style="top:228px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">The&nbsp;coefficients&nbsp;indicate&nbsp;the&nbsp;change&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;log-od</span><span class="mtk1">ds&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;target&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:247px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">variable&nbsp;</span><span class="mtk1 bracket-highlighting-0">(</span><span class="mtk1">being&nbsp;'rich'&nbsp;in&nbsp;'Checking&nbsp;account'</span><span class="mtk1 bracket-highlighting-0">)</span><span class="mtk1">&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;one-unit&nbsp;increase&nbsp;in&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:266px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">the&nbsp;feature,&nbsp;holding&nbsp;all&nbsp;other&nbsp;features&nbsp;constant.&nbsp;</span><span class="mtk1">A&nbsp;positive&nbsp;coefficient&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:285px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">means&nbsp;the&nbsp;feature&nbsp;increases&nbsp;the&nbsp;log-odds&nbsp;of&nbsp;being&nbsp;</span><span class="mtk1">class&nbsp;1,&nbsp;while&nbsp;a&nb